items.title: TCS Q2 results on October 10; board to consider second interim dividend
items.description: TCS will announce its Q2 earnings on October 10, with a potential interim dividend declaration. Despite a gradual recovery in client spending, revenue growth remains stable. MOFSL expects TCS to see a 1% QoQ growth in constant currency. Previous Q1 profits and revenue exceeded expectations.

items.title: Accenture's AI business takes center stage in quarterly results beat
items.description: IT services major Accenture unveiled a $4 billion share buyback on Thursday, closing the fourth quarter with better-than-expected results thanks to strong demand for its services that help businesses adopt generative AI technology.

items.title: Accenture unveils $4 bln share buyback as AI powers strong fourth quarterly revenue
items.description: Accenture Q4 Results 2024: Accenture, headquartered in Dublin, exceeded analyst forecasts by reporting a fourth-quarter revenue of $16.41 billion, surpassing the anticipated $16.38 billion, as per LSEG data.
